					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13866585#post-4821738</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13866585/ronald-reagan-cut-up-while-rapping#post-4821738</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 18 Nov 2020 17:16:19 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>LordStonefish</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2527320</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p><em>No understanding of the person that's being written about. No understanding of hip-hop, either in spirit or artistic structure. Barely an understanding, even in the earlier era in which this written, of what constitutes a good SCP article beyond the immediately identifiable tropes (guys in orange jump suits, scary keter monsters locked up somewhere, spooky XK). I don't know why I never documented my thoughts on this article back when it was first posted, but that was clearly a mistake, because [..] the product isn't really worth a whole lot on its own in the first place.</em> - Kalinin, in the comments of SCP-2137</p> <p><em>This whole thing reads like one of the worse episodes of Epic Rap Battles. [&#8230;] Nah dude. No way</em> - djkaktus, in direct followup.</p> <p>I'm so sorry. I spent three days on this idiocy. I am not a musician, I can sing and play a little piano, so the fact that this is a song at all is a biblical miracle. Again, apologies to your ears.</p> <p>The song contains samples from <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Four_Ruffles_and_Flourishes_and_Hail_to_the_Chief.ogg">The United States Navy Band version of Hail to The Chief</a> (a song in the public domain, itself in the public domain as a work of the U.S. federal government) and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=veFiFo7vBSU">this terrifying deepfake reading of SCP-1981 by youtuber Ekian M</a>. All other sounds are me, an instrument I borrowed, or a Garageband preset.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
